Module flag4j
Package org.flag4j.arrays.backend.field

Class AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T extends AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T,V>,V extends Field<V>>

java.lang.Object
org.flag4j.arrays.backend.AbstractTensor<T,Field<V>[],V>
org.flag4j.arrays.backend.field.AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T,V>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of this dense field tensor.
V - The type of the Field which this tensor's entries belong to.
U - Type of sparse tensor equivalent to T. This type parameter is required because some operations (e.g.
invalid reference 
#toCoo()
) may result in a sparse tensor.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, FieldTensorMixin<T,T,V>, TensorOverField<T,T,Field<V>[],V>, TensorOverRing<T,T,Field<V>[],V>, TensorOverSemiRing<T,T,Field<V>[],V>, TensorBinaryOpsMixin<T,T>, TensorMixin<T,Field<V>[],V>
public abstract class AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T extends AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T,V>,V extends Field<V>> extends AbstractTensor<T,Field<V>[],V> implements FieldTensorMixin<T,T,V>

The base class for all dense Field tensors.

The AbstractTensor.entries of an AbstractDenseFieldTensor are mutable but the AbstractTensor.shape is fixed.

    • tensorTr

      public T tensorTr(int axis1, int axis2)

      Computes the generalized trace of this tensor along the specified axes.

      The generalized tensor trace is the sum along the diagonal values of the 2D sub-arrays of this tensor specified by axis1 and axis2. The shape of the resulting tensor is equal to this tensor with the axis1 and axis2 removed.

      Specified by:
      tensorTr in interface TensorOverSemiRing<T extends AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T,V>,T extends AbstractDenseFieldTensor<T,V>,Field<V extends Field<V>>[],V extends Field<V>>
      Parameters:
      axis1 - First axis for 2D sub-array.
      axis2 - Second axis for 2D sub-array.
      Returns:
      The generalized trace of this tensor along axis1 and axis2.
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the two axes are not both larger than zero and less than this tensors rank.
      IllegalArgumentException - If axis1 == @code axis2 or this.shape.get(axis1) != this.shape.get(axis1) (i.e. the axes are equal or the tensor does not have the same length along the two axes.)
